    "explanation": "'Gli piacciono i film francesi' means 'He likes French films'. Piacere agrees with the thing liked, not the experiencer. Here 'i film' is plural, so piacciono. The experiencer 'he' surfaces as IOP gli.",
    "examiner_note": "Two diagnostic points: (1) verb agrees with plural thing-liked; (2) IOP choice for masculine 3sg liker.",
