    "explanation": "'Anna è in Australia da sei mesi e le manca molto la sua famiglia' means 'Anna has been in Australia for six months and she misses her family a lot'. Mancare follows the piacere pattern: the misser is the experiencer (IOP), the thing missed is the grammatical subject. 'Le manca la famiglia' is literally 'to her is missing the family'.",
    "examiner_note": "Often catches learners who write 'lei manca la famiglia' (English-style).",
