    "explanation": "'La mattina mi alzo alle sette' means 'I get up at seven in the morning'. Italian uses a reflexive verb for actions the subject does to itself. Alzarsi (to get up) is reflexive; 1sg → mi alzo. Surface-identical with DOP/IOP mi, but the verb's reflexivity picks the reading.",
