          "infinitive": {
            "reveal": "divertirsi - to enjoy oneself",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.divertirsi.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Anna si è divertita molto alla festa' means 'Anna really enjoyed herself at the party'. Reflexive verbs take essere as their auxiliary, with the participle showing agreement with the subject. Anna is f.sg → divertita. The clitic si sits pre-aux. Stack: si + è + divertita.",
    "examiner_note": "Cross-references the passato_prossimo tree for the agreement bucket.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_refl_essere_03",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "pronoun",
    "subtopic": "reflexive.essere_in_compound",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Complete: 'I ragazzi ____ ____ lavati le mani prima di cena.' (auxiliary + participle)",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 2,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": false,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "pronoun.reflexive.essere_in_compound",
        "label": "Reflexive aux essere, 3pl",
        "any_phrases": [
          "si sono"
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "hanno",
          "si hanno"
        ]
      },
      {
        "order_index": 1,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "verb_form.passato_prossimo.auxiliary.essere_reflexive",
        "label": "Participle agrees with subject (modern) or with post-verb DO (prescriptive)",
        "any_phrases": [
          "lavati",
          "lavate"
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "lavato",
          "lavata"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "lavati",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "infinitive": {
            "reveal": "lavarsi - to wash oneself",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.lavarsi.translation"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "lemma": "mani",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "mano - hand",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.mano.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'I ragazzi si sono lavati le mani prima di cena' means 'The boys washed their hands before dinner'. Even with a separate direct object (le mani), the reflexive still takes essere as auxiliary. Modern Italian agrees the past participle with the subject (lavati, agreeing with i ragazzi). Older usage and some prescriptive grammars agree it instead with the post-verb direct object (lavate, agreeing with le mani); both are accepted here.",
    "examiner_note": "Both lavati (modern subject agreement) and lavate (prescriptive DO agreement) credit; wrong-gender forms in must_not_include.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_refl_with_obj_01",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "pronoun",
    "subtopic": "reflexive.with_object",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Replace 'le mani': 'Mi lavo le mani.' → '____ lavo.'",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": false,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "pronoun.reflexive.with_object",
        "label": "Reflexive + DOP cluster, with vowel change",
        "any_phrases": [
          "me le"
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "mi le",
          "le mi",
          "me li",
          "mele"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "lavo",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "infinitive": {
            "reveal": "lavarsi - to wash oneself",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.lavarsi.translation"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "lemma": "mani",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "mano - hand",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.mano.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Me le lavo' means 'I wash them (for myself)'. When a reflexive verb has both a subject and a direct object on the side, the two clitics form a cluster. The reflexive mi undergoes the vowel change to me before the DOP. Le mani is f.pl → le. Stack: me + le giving 'me le lavo'.",
    "examiner_note": "Common miss: 'mi le' (no vowel change). Cross-references pronoun.combined.vowel_changes.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_refl_with_obj_02",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "pronoun",
    "subtopic": "reflexive.with_object",
    "difficulty": 3,
    "cefr_level_target": "B2",
    "prompt": "Replace 'i denti': 'Marco si lava i denti.' → 'Marco ____ lava.'",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": false,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "pronoun.reflexive.with_object",
        "label": "Reflexive 3sg + DOP m.pl, vowel change does NOT apply to si",
        "any_phrases": [
          "se li"
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "si li",
          "si le",
          "se le"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [
      {
        "lemma": "denti",
        "language": "it",
        "aspects": {
          "translation": {
            "reveal": "dente - tooth",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.dente.translation"
          },
          "gender": {
            "reveal": "masculine (m)",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.dente.gender"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Marco se li lava' means 'Marco brushes them (his teeth)'. Si + DOP → 'se' before the DOP (the vowel change pattern extends to si: si → se). I denti is m.pl → DOP 'li'. So 'se li lava'.",
    "examiner_note": "Vowel-change pattern: mi/ti/si/ci/vi → me/te/se/ce/ve before another clitic. This is the same family as pronoun.combined.vowel_changes.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_comb_order_01",
