    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'Me lo dai?' means 'Will you give it to me?'. Two rules combine. In a clitic cluster the IOP comes first; and the vowel change shifts mi to me before another clitic. Stack: mi → me, then me + lo, giving 'me lo dai'.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_comb_vowel_01",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "pronoun",
    "subtopic": "combined.vowel_changes",
    "difficulty": 2,
    "cefr_level_target": "B1",
    "prompt": "Combine the pronouns: 'mi + lo' → ____",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": false,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "pronoun.combined.vowel_changes",
        "label": "mi → me before lo",
        "any_phrases": [
          "me lo"
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "mi lo",
          "me li",
          "mi le",
          "melo"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'me lo' = 'it to me'. When two clitics stack, the final -i of mi/ti/ci/vi shifts to -e before the following clitic. This is the vowel change. So mi + lo → me lo.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_comb_vowel_02",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "pronoun",
    "subtopic": "combined.vowel_changes",
    "difficulty": 2,
    "cefr_level_target": "B1",
    "prompt": "Combine the pronouns: 'ti + la' → ____",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": false,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "pronoun.combined.vowel_changes",
        "label": "ti → te before la",
        "any_phrases": [
          "te la"
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "ti la",
          "te le",
          "tela"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'te la' = 'it to you'. The vowel change applies to ti as well: ti + la → te la.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_comb_vowel_03",
    "language_code": "it",
    "topic": "pronoun",
    "subtopic": "combined.vowel_changes",
    "difficulty": 2,
    "cefr_level_target": "B1",
    "prompt": "Combine the pronouns: 'ci + li' → ____",
    "type": "short",
    "marks": 1,
    "prompt_supplies_base_form": false,
    "markpoints": [
      {
        "order_index": 0,
        "credit": 1.0,
        "bucket": "pronoun.combined.vowel_changes",
        "label": "ci → ce before li",
        "any_phrases": [
          "ce li"
        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "ci li",
          "ce le",
          "celi"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'ce li' = 'them to us'. The vowel change applies to all of mi/ti/ci/vi: ci + li → ce li. (The same shift applies whether the ci is IOP, reflexive, or locative.)",
    "examiner_note": "Note: this 'ci' is IOP/reflexive 1pl. The locative ci also undergoes the same change in clusters (ce ne sono = 'there are some').",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
