    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'gliela' = 'it (fem.) to her'. The glielo-family transform applies to BOTH the masculine IOP gli and the feminine IOP le. Both shift to glie- before a DOP. Stack: le + la → gliela. The IOP's gender becomes invisible in the cluster.",
    "examiner_note": "Hot spot. Diagnostic miss: 'le la' (keeping the feminine IOP separate). This is the single most common pronoun error among B1 learners.",
    "version": 1
  },
