      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Me ne vado' means 'I'm off'. Andarsene is a pronominal verb: the reflexive si and the ne are lexicalised into the verb's identity. Conjugation varies the reflexive component by person. 1sg: mi shifts to me before ne. Stack: me + ne + vado.",
    "examiner_note": "Idiomatic. The reflexive component changes per person (mi → me / ti → te / si → se / etc.); ne is invariable.",
    "version": 1
  },
