    "explanation": "'Avete del pane? Sì, ce ne abbiamo molto' means 'Have you got any bread? Yes, we've got lots of it'. The ci here is the existential/locative ci, combined with partitive ne. The vowel change shifts ci to ce. Stack: ce + ne giving 'ce n'è' / 'ce ne sono' / 'ce ne abbiamo'.",
    "examiner_note": "Some grammarians would bucket this under existentials rather than the personal-IOP cluster; both flavours use the same surface form. The bucket tagged here is me_ne_family as the surface-pattern home.",
    "version": 1
  },
