    ],
    "explanation": "'Quanti fratelli hai? Ne ho due' means 'How many brothers do you have? I have two of them'. When you drop a noun after a quantifier (number, un po', molti), Italian requires the partitive ne to resume it. 'Ho due' alone isn't grammatical; the partitive ne is obligatory.",
    "examiner_note": "Common miss: omitting ne entirely ('ho due'). The bucket records that failure.",
    "version": 1
  },
