          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Compri il pane? No, ne compro solo un po'' means 'Are you buying the bread? No, I'm only buying a little of it'. Italian distinguishes the whole-object reading (DOP lo = the whole loaf) from the partitive reading (ne = some of it). The quantifier 'un po'' signals the partitive, so the partitive ne is required.",
