    "explanation": "'Cosa pensi del nuovo film? Ne penso che sia bellissimo' means 'What do you think of the new film? I think it's really beautiful'. Italian pensare DI means 'have an opinion about'. The pronominal ne replaces the di-phrase. 'Cosa ne pensi?' is the stock question. (Pensare A is different and takes ci.)",
