    "explanation": "'Sei sicuro di quello che dici? Sì, ne sono sicuro' means 'Are you sure of what you're saying? Yes, I'm sure of it'. The adjective sicuro takes 'di + thing' for what one is sure of. The pronominal ne stands in for the di-complement here, not just for verbal di-complements.",
    "version": 1
