          },
          "gender": {
            "reveal": "feminine (f)",
            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.mela.gender"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Hai mangiato le mele? Sì, ne ho mangiate tre' means 'Have you eaten the apples? Yes, I've eaten three of them'. The partitive ne triggers participle agreement with its antecedent. Le mele is f.pl → mangiate. This is one of the few cases where the participle agrees with avere as auxiliary, exactly parallel to the preceding-DOP rule.",
    "examiner_note": "Hot spot. Cross-references verb_form.passato_prossimo.participle_agreement.with_avere.preceding_partitive_ne. Common miss: 'mangiato' (default m.sg).",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
