    "explanation": "'Ieri c'è stata molta gente al concerto' means 'Yesterday there were lots of people at the concert'. The existential takes essere as auxiliary in compound tenses, with the participle showing agreement. Gente is a collective f.sg → c'è stata. Italian uses essere here, not avere (the English 'there was/had' pattern is misleading).",
