    "explanation": "'Non ce la faccio' means 'I can't manage it'. Farcela is a pronominal verb meaning 'to manage / make it'. Both clitics are lexicalised. The vowel change shifts ci to ce before la. Stack: ce + la + faccio, giving 'non ce la faccio' for 1sg negative.",
