    "explanation": "'Pensi spesso a tua nonna? Ci penso ogni giorno' means 'Do you often think about your grandma? I think about her every day'. Pensare A takes an a-phrase, replaced by the locative ci. (Pensare DI, with the sense of opinion, would take pronominal ne.) The preposition picks the clitic.",
