    "explanation": "'Lo vedo ogni giorno' means 'I see him every day'. In any finite tense, the clitic sits in pre-verb position, immediately before the verb. The English-style 'vedo lo' isn't grammatical.",
    "examiner_note": "Most basic position rule. Common miss: 'vedo lo'.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
