    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'Glielo voglio dare' means 'I want to give it to him'. With a modal verb + infinitive, a clitic cluster moves as a whole. Either pre-verb before the modal ('glielo voglio dare') or attached to the infinitive ('voglio darglielo'). The cluster never splits, never sits between.",
    "examiner_note": "Common miss: 'voglio glielo dare' (between modal and inf). Cross-references combined-cluster rules.",
