            "bucket": "vocabulary.it.sapere.translation"
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Sai che oggi è domenica? Sì, lo so' means 'Do you know that today is Sunday? Yes, I know'. When the 'it' refers back to a whole clause, Italian uses neuter lo. Invariable regardless of the antecedent's gender. The lo is obligatory; 'Sì, so' alone isn't grammatical.",
    "examiner_note": "Common miss: 'Sì, so' (omitting lo). The clause resumption is obligatory.",
    "version": 1
  },
  {
    "external_id": "op_spec_lo_neut_02",
