    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'Ieri non ti ho visto al bar' means 'I didn't see you at the bar yesterday'. The 2sg DOP ti sits in pre-verb position before the auxiliary. With 1sg/2sg/1pl/2pl DOPs the past participle stays invariable in modern usage (older agreement-with-clitic is now marked).",
    "examiner_note": "Modern usage prefers invariable participle with mi/ti/ci/vi. Some grammars accept 'ti ho vista' for a female 'you' but it's marked.",
    "version": 1
  },
