    "explanation": "'Marco mi aveva promesso un libro. Ieri me l'ha dato finalmente' means 'Marco had promised me a book. Yesterday he finally gave it to me'. The first sentence sets up 'a me' as the recipient and 'un libro' as the masculine singular object. In passato prossimo the cluster sits pre-auxiliary. The vowel change shifts mi to me before another pronoun, and lo undergoes elision to l' before ha. Stack: me + l' + ha + dato.",
    "examiner_note": "Single answer slot accepts both 'me l'' (elided, standard) and 'me lo' (unelided). The joined form 'melo' is in must_not_include as the joined-when-separate diagnostic.",
    "version": 1
  },
