    ],
    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'La verità? Gliel'ho già detta' means 'The truth? I've already told him/her'. Inside the cluster gliela, the DOP is la (f.sg, referring to 'la verità'). Participle agreement with the preceding f.sg DOP gives detta. The elision gliela → gliel' before ho hides the -a, but the agreement still surfaces on the participle.",
    "examiner_note": "Tests that even when the cluster's elision hides the DOP gender, the participle still encodes it.",
    "version": 1
  },
