    "explanation": "'Gliene dai?' means 'Will you give him some?'. The glielo-family transform applies to ne too: gli + ne → gliene, as one word. The verb dare goes in the present (dai) or future (darai); both work in the question frame.",
    "examiner_note": "Two markpoints: gliene cluster choice and dare verb form. Tests gliene in a question frame, distinct from glielo declaratives.",
