          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "explanation": "'Hai bevuto del vino? Sì, ne ho bevuto un bicchiere' means 'Have you drunk any wine? Yes, I've drunk a glass of it'. Vino is m.sg → partitive ne agreement m.sg → bevuto (-o ending; here invariable-looking but it IS agreement). The 'ne ho bevuti' distractor would be wrong (m.pl agreement for a m.sg antecedent).",
    "examiner_note": "Tests that the participle agrees with the antecedent's gender/number, not just defaulting to -o. With m.sg the ending happens to match the invariable default, but it's still the agreement rule applied.",
