    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'Hai parlato con tre amici? Sì, ne ho parlato' means 'Have you spoken with three friends? Yes, I've spoken about them'. Critical diagnostic: pronominal ne (for di-phrases like 'parlare di') does NOT trigger participle agreement. Only PARTITIVE ne does. So 'ne ho parlato' (invariable), not 'ne ho parlati'.",
    "examiner_note": "Hot diagnostic. The fact that ne can be partitive OR pronominal-di, and ONLY partitive triggers agreement, is a frequent confusion at B2.",
    "version": 1
  },
