        ],
        "must_not_include": [
          "diggliene",
          "di gliene"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'digliene' = 'tell him about it'. The gli-exception to consonant doubling carries through to clusters: gli still doesn't double. Stack: di' + gli + ne → digliene (one word, no doubling on gli). The diglielo distractor would use neuter lo for 'it', not ne for 'about it'.",
    "examiner_note": "Extends the gli-exception rule to a cluster. The cluster gli + ne becomes gliene (one word).",
    "version": 1
  },
