          "tu"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'Senza di te, non posso farcela' means 'Without you, I can't manage it'. After senza, Italian uses the stressed pronoun. The preferred form inserts an optional di: 'senza di te'. Plain 'senza te' is also standard. 'Senza ti' (clitic) isn't grammatical.",
    "examiner_note": "Tests a different preposition (senza) than the earlier 'con me' item. Notes: 'senza di te' is the more common standard form.",
    "version": 1
  },
