    "explanation": "'Ha invitato me, non lui' means 'She invited me, not him'. Italian uses the stressed pronoun post-verb for strong contrastive emphasis. The plain clitic mi can't carry contrast: 'Ha invitato me, non lui' puts the focus on the speaker. The clitic-plus-stressed doubling ('Mi ha invitato me') exists but is more marked.",
