          "Me-le"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "vocab_help": [],
    "explanation": "'Le scarpe? Me le ho lavate stamattina' means 'The shoes? I washed them for myself this morning'. In passato prossimo the cluster sits pre-aux and stays as a separated cluster (two words). The reflexive mi shifts to me before the DOP le. Participle agreement with f.pl gives lavate. Stack: me + le + ho + lavate.",
    "examiner_note": "Tests the rule with reflexive + DOP cluster in PP. Combines the joined/separate rule with participle agreement.",
  